;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
;; Integration: Git Worktree Common Dir
;; Minimal support for running inside a linked Git worktree.
;; Source: 50-integrations-core/worktree-common-dir.sb
;; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

;; Why this exists:
;; A linked Git worktree can keep refs, the index, and worktree bookkeeping
;; under a shared git common dir outside the selected workdir. Without access
;; to that shared metadata, normal git commands from the active worktree fail
;; even though the checkout itself is already writable.
;;
;; Limitations:
;; - Detection happens once when Safehouse launches the wrapped process.
;; - This only grants the active worktree's shared git common dir when the
;;   selected workdir itself resolves to a Git worktree root.
;; - Sibling worktree files are handled separately by the default `worktrees`
;;   integration and remain read-only.
;;
;; Runtime snapshot (this placeholder comment line is replaced at launch):
;;   shared git common dir: __SAFEHOUSE_REPLACE_ME_WITH_GIT_WORKTREE_COMMON_DIR_STATUS__
;;
;; Example generated rules (illustrative only; actual paths depend on launch):
;;   (allow file-read* file-write* (subpath "/Users/alice/src/project/.git"))
;;
;; Runtime-generated rules are emitted immediately below this profile section.
